  "description": "Follow-up scheduling logic for cervical cancer screening CDS. Determines post-treatment follow-up timing (12 months, both populations), post-triage-negative follow-up timing (12 months WLHIV, 24 months general), WLHIV double follow-up tracking, return-to-routine criteria, and re-entry to triage/treatment when follow-up HPV retest is positive. Covers WHO Recommendations 11-13 (general) and 31-33 (WLHIV).",
